\pard\f0\fs28 {\b P. jeffreyi} Grev. & Balf. in A. Murray,{\i  Bot. Exped. Oreg.}{\b  8:} 2 (1853), from W. North America, a tree up to 60 m, with nonresinous buds, glaucous twigs, greyish- to bluish-green leaves 12-20 cm, cone 15-25 cm, and the umbo with a recurved mucro, is also occasionally cultivated, sometimes under the name of{\i  P. ponderosa}.
