\pard\f0\fs28 {\b P. sabiniana }Douglas, {\i Trans. Linn. Soc. London }({\i Bot.}){\b  16:} 749 (1833), from California, a tree up to 25 m, with lax habit, sparse, pale green leaves 20-30 cm, and cone 15-25 cm, is cultivated for timber on a small scale in Europe.
