\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 6. P. nigra} Arnold,{\i  Reise Mariazell} 8 (1785) ({\i P. maritima} Miller). Tree up to 50 m; bark grey to dark brown. Buds ovoid or cylindrical-ovoid, acute, slightly resinous. Twigs glabrous, pale brown to orange-brown. Leaves 4-19 cm × 1-2 mm, in pairs, light or dark green, somewhat rigid, flexuous, straight or curved; 1-5 layers of hypodermal cells; resin-canals 3-17, median. Cone 3-8 × 2-4 cm, yellowish- or light brown, shining, subsessile; apophysis slightly or obtusely keeled; umbo mucronate. 2n = 24.{\i  S. Europe, extending northwards to Austria and S. Carpathians; extensively planted in N. Europe} ({\i especially subsp.} ({\b c})){\i  for timber or shelter.} Al Au Bu Co Ga Gr Hs It Ju Rm Rs(K) Si Tu [Be Br Cz Da Ge Hb He Ho Su].
